    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Demo 2 — Retail Revenue Mart\n\nA mini-ETL: aggregate the last 14 days of `RETAIL.SALES` (~585M rows) into a small reporting table, **idempotently** — re-running refreshes the same 14 rows instead of duplicating them.\n\n**Expected output:** upsert reports `affectedRows: 14`; read-back returns exactly 14 items on every run.",
        "height": 280,
        "width": 900,
        "color": 5
      },
      "id": "d2s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000001",
      "name": "Sticky Note",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -80,
        -460
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Resolve the write schema\n\nNothing is hardcoded: `SELECT COALESCE(CURRENT_SCHEMA, CURRENT_USER)` returns your credential’s *Default Schema*, or falls back to the schema named after your database user.\n\nSet the credential’s Default Schema to redirect all writes.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 260
      },
      "id": "d2s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000002",
      "name": "Sticky Note2",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        270,
        -160
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### DDL needs the guard off\n\nOne of only two nodes in the example set with *Restrict to SELECT Queries* **disabled** — required for `CREATE TABLE`.\n\n`IF NOT EXISTS` keeps existing rows so the upsert has history to merge into.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "id": "d2s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000003",
      "name": "Sticky Note3",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        570,
        -160
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Aggregate at the source\n\nGroups ~585M rows by day and keeps the newest 14 dates. The UPPERCASE column aliases match the mart’s column names exactly — that’s what *Auto-Map Input Data* in the next node relies on.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 260
      },
      "id": "d2s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000004",
      "name": "Sticky Note4",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        870,
        -160
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Create or Update (MERGE)\n\nExasol has no `INSERT ON CONFLICT`; the node generates `MERGE INTO … USING (VALUES …)`. *Conflict Columns* = `SALES_DATE`: existing dates are updated, new dates inserted.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 260
      },
      "id": "d2s00000-0000-4000-8000-900000000005",
      "name": "Sticky Note5",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        1170,
        -160
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "### Select Rows\n\nA structured SELECT built from collections: WHERE (`REVENUE > 0`) and sort (`SALES_DATE DESC`) — no SQL written by hand.",
        "height": 360,
        "width": 260
      },
